By: Ibn 'Arabi
---
This immense thought (of the ‘Supreme Identity’) is only befitting to him
whose soul is vaster than the two worlds. As for him whose soul is only as
vast as the two worlds, it befits him not. For in truth this thought is greater
than the sensible world and the supra-sensible world both taken together.
